songLongImpressions.Comment: Amazing submission from TAG and ShakeJ!This song has the signature TAG style that is easily recognizable, but still stands out with a pleasant melody. I especially enjoyed the piano verse near the end. It's nice to hear modern TAG paired with a BGA is visually appealing and somewhat reminiscent of old BEMANI visuals, which I thought was a cool touch. (Hyper difficulties played only) Charting is very well done, I appreciate the effort to reach more players by including the other keymodes that are not supported.The only complaints I have are the kicks at the end of the song, which are a bit strong and came across as out of place. In addition, the BGA cut-ins with the black text on a white background does not jive with the wild nature of the rest of the BGA, so that could have more effort put into it.In summary, this is a great track! I hope to see it get licensed by many games in the months to come!

First of all, out of all tracks you wrote while being a freelancer, that's definitely one of your stongest works. It's dynamic, energetic yet has its gentle piano moments as a breather which I really appreciate. It's a really nice track to come back to every once in a while.The BGA is also phenomenal and I really dig its retro-futuristic aesthetics with hints of abstact art.  The chart (I played SPA) is servicable. It's simplistic and a bit repetitive but there's nothing wrong with that considering it's a long track. Speaking of which...I deducted 50 points of going over the limit of 2:30. I'm sorry, but rhythm games have adopted 2:00-2:30 length for a track as a standart for a reason.  Overall, thank you TAG for making this 20th BMS event even more monumental! You music is always welcome and I don't think I have should have wasted any words by explaining the obvious - this track ROCKS HARD.

299.songComment: (2024å¹´10æœˆ20æ—¥ 14:45 æ›´æ–°)(2024å¹´10æœˆ20æ—¥ 08:12 æ›´æ–°)I had a lot of fun making this song and BGA, and I hope you all have fun playing it!This song is based off the original Zilla World game that can be found at https://scratch.mit.edu/projects/574305691This song still keeps some original sound, but has been remastered to have more order while maintaining its random rhythms.But I'm pretty sure that after making three BMS songs, that's just my style, I mostly make random rhythms.The BMS was also originally supposed to be complete about two weeks ago, but a hurricane hit the entire group and caused voice recordings to be pushed back last minute.Anyways, we all survived, and that's all that matters.I worked hard on this BMS, but please leave all of your critiques so I can improve!*Since it won't let me fit everything in the name section, I want to credit the people who did the vocals with me:Birdzilla- SelineDonut Doggie/Donut Dog Robot- ExtraVirginOliveOil

69.songComment: (2024å¹´10æœˆ06æ—¥ 00:05 æ›´æ–°)"Hello! This is a song I made with my friend andromaeda, who sang and wrote the melody and lyrics. It's a funky little house tune with a tropical vibe and a little bit of a spooky, abstract twist for flavour. For this song, we were inspired strongly by the laid-back rhythms of the OutRun soundtrack (this is probably obvious from the song's title, LOL), as well as Soichi Terada's quirky but hard-hitting house tracks! The lyrics for this song are actually quite existential, with a strong theme of "ego death"; I tried to reflect this by adding all sorts of eerie little sounds, riffs, loops, and distortions that refract and respond to andromaeda's crystalline voice. I think the result is unique but also fun and groovy!! I hope you enjoy it." - Baby Zionov"Hello! I made this song with Baby Zionov after I wrote the original demo. I wanted to write a song that sounded like 90s Japanese House music (such as Soichi Terada) and video game OSTs such as OutRun and Sonic the Hedgehog, since it is a style that I like. I also enjoy experimental music, so I found a way to use those aspects as well. I wrote the lyrics as a way to process all the feelings I had about a bad experience, in a way that also admits the mistakes I made. Baby Zionov was wonderful to work with, and she added so many cool ideas to the song that I wouldn't have thought of myself. She expertly produced the song and it would not sound the way it would without her!" - andromaeda

songLongImpressions.Comment: Honestly, your style is so unique and weirdly attractive, it's hard to explain.First of all, I really like Lemon Magnolia for its chill vibes, Dolphin Diamond Raceway for its bright yet funky summer vibes and PJ Princess for ...let's say a lot of things that were intentially put there under the disguise of a seemingly childish song about boredom which gradually spirals into dark tones, hinting at isolating depression. I feel like Magical Meteor Sound Shower is a spiritual sequel (correct me if I'm wrong) to PJ Princess, since it's no longer about dark tones or depression, that phase is long gone. It's about 'not caring' anymore to the point where you just move to the beat and go with the flow regardless of how you feel.The chorus is something special, the vocals really shine there! The visual imagery is more suggestive and straight-forward this time around, which isn't bad at all! It was nice seeing so many contrasting and rich colours compared to what you did before. The chart is also quite good! Thank you for your hard work. Consider me a fan ;)

songLongImpressions.Comment: This is the best work I've heard in YEARS in BMS of Fighters. Very reminiscent of SHIKI's Orfevre but that's not a bad thing in the slightest. The only track I keep listening to on repeat since its initial release. The BGA is also stunning!Chart (Played) SPA is servicable and nothing spectacular. Az3's here.I tried to follow the leader of the team, L216, the intended theme for the team.If I could recall the theme, it should be "Dedication for the SuperFans".It was the theme where I should make something that refers to something.Movies, Communities, Music, anything.And this time, I picked out Object Show Communities as a tribute of something that I grew up since childhood.The BGA might be simple, and that is the charm especially for an OSC.The entire BGA was made in Canva, and I've decided to pick out story telling with a hint of moral lesson.That usually is common with these cartoonish shows, though almost few to none are visible in OSC videos.But, I tried my best. songLongImpressions.Comment: I have seen many NSFW entries before, and they all create content with care. However, in your work, I have only seen pure jumpscare, which is the lowest level, and it seems that BGA is not your original work, because I know this is a long circulated jumpscare video.When I was playing, even if I only saw BGA with my peripheral vision, I almost died. songLongImpressions.Comment: Really enjoyed your track, quite energetic with deep bass and simple yet effective melody.I feel like having some kind of even simplistic BGA with emergency sirens and the radiation sign spinning in the background could make the track more impactiful.Thank you for your hard work!

That was really brave. An original interpretation of an old classic beatmania track.And you know what? I really dig it! Not only did you write original lyrics for the whole track adding the all too recognizable 'YOU CAN' to make the reference more obvious, but you still completely changed the mood of the original track and for some reason...it works really well!Melancholic vibes, spicy voice chords near the chorus and phenomenal BGA that manages to be both modern, stylish and at the same time very reminiscent of the old style of animations used in 5K beatmania, especially that last animation.The chart is more than serviceable.Overall, this work is something! Good balance between the old and the new! You did something unique that's for sure!Thank you for your hard work!

songShortImpressions.Content: [SPA Played] For me, this is the best song and chart of the contest and the only one I'll be giving a perfect score to. Not only is this an incredibly well written and well charted score, it's also very nostalgic and reminds me of old megaman music. I've been listening to this for the month leading up to impressions and only came to enjoy it more once the BMS was released. I enjoyed the BGA as well!

songLongImpressions.Comment: What I can see is that all of the effort was put into making a great BGA - it's stunning, that much I can tell. Lots of effects and everything looks extremely polished and neat.That said, the music itself leaves a lot to be desired and doesn't keep up with the quality of BGA. It does sound like an indie effort we'd see in MUMEI ACADEMY moreso than a mature composition. Lots of muffled instruments, lackcluster and slow development, and a rather mediocre melody.

songShortImpressions.Content: [SPA, SPH] [Song 350/400, Chart 375/400, Visuals 100/100] A very emotional work! Awesome job!

songLongImpressions.Comment: Love the desolate and isolated vibe of the song. I really like the part with the acid sounds in the middle as well as the melancholic piano after that. The song does a great job of having emotional highs and lows. The BGA is really nice, I love the space visuals as I feel they complement the song very well.Good work!

First of all, it is NOT Hard Renaissance. Not in the slightest.It's a very niche genre with fixed set of rules where adding piano alone isn't gonna cut it. Your track is more of a regular hardcore kind with orchestral vibes near the end. Flower by Dj Yoshitaka, PUPA by Morimori Atsushii, Wagamama Princess by Er, BABYLON by SHIKI, Halcyon by xi are all great examples of Hard Renaissance.That said, I can't say I didn't enjoy what I heard. It's a decent hardcore track (minus the second part) with servicable visuals. Played SPA, really enjoyed the chart.Thank you for your hard work!

I love the composition in this one! I wish the mix was a bit better though, as the low end is kind of muddy. Other than the minor mixing issues, I love everything about this! The combination of the melody and the progression gave me goosebumps when I first heard it. The chart is fun too. Great work!

songShortImpressions.Content: Super powerful kicks and a great vibe with a cool BGA. I have minor issues with the charting of the hyper but it's still fun to play. Good work!

songLongImpressions.Comment: One of my favourite works this year. Amazing HI-TECH track. Dynamic, energetic, light and catchy melody.The BGA is absolutely top-notch. Stylish and goes along the track really well!However, (played SPA) the chart is very underwhemling and felt rushed. 1096 notes for almost a 2 minute track and it still manages to be Another 12? That's a sign that something went oh so wrong. In a lot of places (especially the calm middle section) there were so many opportunities to emphisize that beautiful gentle melody (star sparkles, you get what I mean) with some kind of delicate stairs but instead you opted for a simple solution of adding one long note and very few quiet bass notes. That felt very unsatisfying, knowing how much was going on in the background and main melody. I'm still giving you 900 points because music + presentation is easy top-notch. Could have easily been a 1000 pts work if not for a lackcluster SPA chart.Anyway, thank you for your hard work! I'll be rooting for you!
